===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|dormous}}, of uncertain origin. Possibly from {{m|enm||dor-}}, from {{der|en|non|dár||benumbed}} + {{m|enm|mous||mouse}}. More at {{l|en|doze}}, {{l|en|mouse}}. 

The word is sometimes considered to come from an {{cog|xno|-}} derivative of {{cog|fro|dormir||to sleep}} (as {{m|xno|*dormouse||tending to be dormant}}, with second element mistaken for ''mouse''), but no such Anglo-Norman word is known to have existed.<ref>Random House Dictionary, dormouse.</ref>

